John Trevor Key (10 July 1947 – 6 December 1995) was a British photographer and designer, best known for his work for musical artists of the 1970s and 1980s.
One of his best-known covers was for Mike Oldfield's 1973 debut album Tubular Bells.
He died of a brain tumour in December 1995.
